# Project Report: PaperHunt

**Version:** 1.0  
**Date:** 2025-12-17

---

## 1. Software Requirements Specification (SRS)

### 1.1 Introduction
**PaperHunt** is a full-stack web application designed to democratize access to academic research. It enables users to search for research papers, generate AI-powered summaries, manage a personal library, and connect with research opportunities.

### 1.2 Functional Requirements

#### Authentication & User Management
*   **FR-01: Signup**: Users must be able to register with Full Name, Email, and Password.
*   **FR-02: Signin**: Users must be able to authenticate using Email and Password. Successful login returns a JWT in a secure HTTP-only cookie.
*   **FR-03: Signout**: authenticated users can log out, clearing the session cookie.
*   **FR-04: Session Persistence**: The system must validate the token on page load to maintain user sessions.

#### Research Paper Management
*   **FR-05: Search**: Users can search for papers via external APIs (OpenAlex) using keywords.
*   **FR-06: Library Management**: Users can add papers to their personal library with custom bookmarks and categories.
*   **FR-07: Library CRUD**: Users can view, update details (category/bookmark), and remove papers from their library.
*   **FR-08: Filter**: Users can filter their library papers by title or author.

#### AI Features
*   **FR-09: Summarization**: The system uses Google Gemini to generate structured summaries (Introduction, Findings, etc.) for selected papers.
*   **FR-10**: Summaries should be cached in Redis to improve performance.

#### Research Opportunities
*   **FR-11: Create Opportunity**: Authenticated users can post research collaboration opportunities (Title, Description, Skills, Duration).
*   **FR-12: View Opportunities**: Users can browse a list of active research opportunities.

### 1.3 Non-Functional Requirements
*   **Security**: Passwords must be hashed (bcrypt). API routes must be protected via JWT authentication.
*   **Performance**: Redis caching should be used to minimize repeated AI API calls.
*   **Usability**: The frontend should be responsive and user-friendly (React-based).
*   **Reliability**: The system should gracefully handle external API failures (OpenAlex, Gemini).

---

## 2. Software Design Document (SDD)

### 2.1 System Architecture
PaperHunt utilizes a **MERN Stack** (MongoDB, Express.js, React, Node.js) with a **Client-Server** architecture.

*   **Frontend**: React Single Page Application (SPA) utilizing Vite for build tooling. Handles UI rendering and state management.
*   **Backend**: Node.js/Express REST API. Handles business logic, authentication, and external API communication.
*   **Database**: MongoDB (NoSQL) for storing user data, libraries, and opportunities.
*   **Cache**: Redis key-value store for caching AI-generated summaries.

### 2.2 Database Schema Design

#### Users Collection (`users`)
Stores user account information and their personal library (embedded document pattern).

| Field | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `_id` | ObjectId | Unique identifier |
| `fullName` | String | User's full name |
| `email` | String | Unique email address |
| `password` | String | Hashed password |
| `papers` | Array | Embedded array of Paper objects |
| `createdAt` | Date | Timestamp |

**Paper Schema (Embedded in User)**
| Field | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `title` | String | Title of the paper |
| `authors` | Array[String] | List of authors |
| `category` | String | User-assigned category |
| `bookmark` | String | User-assigned bookmark/tag |
| `doi` | String | Digital Object Identifier |
| `pdfLink` | String | Direct link to PDF |

#### Research Collection (`research`)
Stores research opportunities posted by users.

| Field | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `_id` | ObjectId | Unique identifier |
| `title` | String | Title of the opportunity |
| `description` | String | Detailed description |
| `skillsRequired` | Array[String] | List of required skills |
| `membersNeeded` | Number | Count of members needed |
| `status` | String | 'open' or 'closed' |
| `createdBy` | ObjectId | Ref to `User` |

### 2.3 API Design (Key Endpoints)

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Auth Required |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `POST` | `/api/auth/signup` | Register a new user | No |
| `POST` | `/api/auth/signin` | Log in a user | No |
| `POST` | `/api/user/add` | Add paper to library | Yes |
| `GET` | `/api/user/library` | Get user's library | Yes |
| `PATCH` | `/api/user/update/:pid` | Update paper details | Yes |
| `DELETE` | `/api/user/delete/:pid` | Remove paper from library | Yes |

