## 3. Test Cases

### 3.1 Decision Table Testing
**Function Under Test:** [signin](file:///c:/Users/hp/OneDrive/Desktop/projects/AI-mixed/PaperHunt/PaperHunt/backend/controllers/auth.controller.js#50-97) (Auth Controller)

**Logic:**
1.  Check if token already exists in cookies.
2.  If no token, check if email/password provided.
3.  Check if user exists in Database.
4.  Check if password matches hash.

| Condition | Use Case 1 | Use Case 2 | Use Case 3 | Use Case 4 | Use Case 5 |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| Valid Token in Cookie? | Yes | No | No | No | No |
| Email Provided? | N/A | No | Yes | Yes | Yes |
| Password Provided? | N/A | No | No | Yes | Yes |
| User Exists in DB? | N/A | N/A | N/A | No | Yes |
| Password Matches? | N/A | N/A | N/A | N/A | No |
| **Action / Result** | **Auto-Login** | **Error 400** | **Error 400** | **Error 400** | **Error 400** |

**Use Case 6 (Success):** No Token, Email Provided, Password Provided, User Exists, Password Matches -> **Success 200 (New Token)**.

### 3.2 Robust Testing
**Function Under Test:** [addPaperToLibrary](file:///c:/Users/hp/OneDrive/Desktop/projects/AI-mixed/PaperHunt/PaperHunt/backend/controllers/library.controller.js#4-26) (Library Controller)
**Objective:** Verify system behavior under invalid or unexpected input conditions.

| Test ID | Description | Input Data | Expected Output |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **RB-01** | Missing Title | `{ category: "AI", bookmark: "read" }` | `400 Bad Request` ("All fields are required") |
| **RB-02** | Missing Category | `{ title: "Paper 1", bookmark: "read" }` | `400 Bad Request` ("All fields are required") |
| **RB-03** | Missing Bookmark | `{ title: "Paper 1", category: "AI" }` | `400 Bad Request` ("All fields are required") |
| **RB-04** | Missing Optional Fields | `{ title: "P1", category: "C1", bookmark: "B1" }` | `200 OK` (Defaults: DOI="N/A", PDF="N/A", Authors=[]) |
| **RB-05** | Unauthorized User | `{ title: "P1"... }` (No JWT) | `401/500` (Middleware rejection or User Not Found) |
| **RB-06** | Malformed JSON | `{"title": "P1", "category": ...` (Unclosed brace) | `400 Bad Request` (Express JSON parser error) |

### 3.3 Equivalence Class Testing
**Function Under Test:** [signup](file:///c:/Users/hp/OneDrive/Desktop/projects/AI-mixed/PaperHunt/PaperHunt/backend/controllers/auth.controller.js#11-49) (Auth Controller)
**Fields:** `email`, `password`

**Class Partitions:**

| Input | Valid Equivalence Class | Invalid Equivalence Class |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Email** | Valid format (`test@example.com`) | Missing (`null`), Empty (`""`), No domain (`test@`), No user (`@example.com`) |
| **Password** | Non-empty string | Missing (`null`), Empty (`""`) |
| **User State** | New User (Email not in DB) | Existing User (Email already in DB) |

**Test Cases:**
1.  **Valid**: `user="new", email="valid@test.com", pass="123"` -> **201 Created**.
2.  **Invalid Email**: `user="new", email="invalid", pass="123"` -> **400 Bad Request** (if validation exists) or DB Error.
3.  **Existing User**: `user="exists", email="duplicate@test.com", pass="123"` -> **400 Bad Request** ("User already exists").
4.  **Empty Password**: `user="new", email="valid@test.com", pass=""` -> **400 Bad Request**.

### 3.4 Worst Case Testing
**Function Under Test:** [addPaperToLibrary](file:///c:/Users/hp/OneDrive/Desktop/projects/AI-mixed/PaperHunt/PaperHunt/backend/controllers/library.controller.js#4-26) / [getLibraryPapers](file:///c:/Users/hp/OneDrive/Desktop/projects/AI-mixed/PaperHunt/PaperHunt/backend/controllers/library.controller.js#27-39)
**Objective:** Test system interaction at upper limits.

| Test ID | Description | Scenario | Expected Behavior |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **WC-01** | Database Capacity (Doc Size) | User adds 10,000 papers to their library array. | MongoDB max document size (16MB) might be approached. System should handle or pagination should be implemented (currently full array fetch). **Risk: Slow API response.** |
| **WC-02** | Network Latency | [addPaper](file:///c:/Users/hp/OneDrive/Desktop/projects/AI-mixed/PaperHunt/PaperHunt/backend/controllers/library.controller.js#4-26) called with massive title string (e.g., 1MB text). | Server accepts or rejects based on body-parser limits. DB might reject if string is too long (though String type is flexible). |
| **WC-03** | Concurrent Writes | User sends 100 [addPaper](file:///c:/Users/hp/OneDrive/Desktop/projects/AI-mixed/PaperHunt/PaperHunt/backend/controllers/library.controller.js#4-26) requests simultaneously. | MongoDB handles locking. Verify no race conditions lead to lost data or corrupted array. |
